      "content": "I can optimize the function by using a dynamic programming approach, which significantly reduces the time complexity. This way, the function will pass the runtime check for large inputs. Here's the optimized code:\n\n```python\ndef longest_palindrome(s):\n    n = len(s)\n    if n == 0:\n        return \"\"\n    \n    dp = [[False] * n for _ in range(n)]\n    res = \"\"\n    \n    for i in range(n):\n        dp[i][i] = True\n        res = s[i]\n    \n    for i in range(n-1):\n        if s[i] == s[i+1]:\n            dp[i][i+1] = True\n            res = s[i:i+2]\n    \n    for length in range(3, n+1):\n        for i in range(n-length+1):\n            j = i + length - 1\n            if s[i] == s[j] and dp[i+1][j-1]:\n                dp[i][j] = True\n                res = s[i:j+1]\n    \n    return res\n```\n\nThis code uses a 2D array `dp` to store whether a substring is a palindrome. It iteratively builds up the solution",
